        <p>We understand that today’s classroom presents a unique challenge, with technology ranging from decades old projectors to highly sophisticated tablets and computers. Not to mention a confusing mass of wires and lack of simple connectivity between devices. That in itself presents a dilemma. Incorporating technology separated by decades of innovation can be frustratingly time consuming for even the most tech savvy teacher. Time most teachers just don’t have.</p>
