        <p>With today's rapid evolution of technology and teaching methods you need more than just a simple whiteboard and overhead projector.  Our schools are trying to keep up with technology like media projectors, interactive whiteboards, modern Wi-Fi, and classroom audio systems.  Just when you think you've got it all figured out we throw in iPads, Android tablets, and Chromebooks into the mix.  At first, it's incredibly exciting, but that excitement soon wears off when you try to use all of these independent technologies together on a daily basis.  Our team at LUMOS has spent years working with technology in education and know firsthand that if you're not battling Wi-Fi, you're dealing with dead batteries in your microphone, lost remote controls, or trying to figure out which input you need or wire to plug in to display what you want.  Often times it seems like half the class is spent fiddling with the technology that is supposed to make your teaching more dynamic and impactful.  These frustrations led to the development of the SmartHub.</p>
        <img class="img-bg" src="https://images.indiegogo.com/file_attachments/674135/files/20140625070024-04-enlighten-education.jpg?1403704824">
        <p>To help get you back to teaching, we created a device to control all of the technology you use on a daily basis to instruct in your classroom. We then developed an app for Android and iOS  that allows you to control it at just the touch of a screen. So how does it work?</p>
        <img src="https://images.indiegogo.com/file_attachments/674142/files/20140625070226-07-effortlessly-integrate.jpg?1403704946" style="width: 60%">
        <p>From a teachers standpoint, it works great! Let me explain why... to start off, we know you have a stack of equipment needing to be projected to your screen. We've got you covered with 1 VGA and 2 HMDI inputs allowing you to connect both new and old devices to the SmartHub. Next we added a VGA and HDMI outputs so it can be connected to your existing projector, no matter how old it is. We followed that up by adding a dedicated Wi-Fi hotspot for the teacher so that no students or even teachers from other classrooms will bog down your connection. We've also included a sleek and modern wireless microphone and outputs for up to four speakers.  If you don't have speakers in your class already, don't worry, we can give you those too.  I know you're thinking "now that's all great and dandy.... but you said this thing was smart".  To control all of this wizardry we put in an Android operating system and built custom software allowing you to wirelessly mirror or extend you screen from any mobile device to the projector.  We figured it's 2014, you should be able to share your screen without having to plug in a cable!  Last but not least, we are developing an app giving you complete control of the system at the touch of a finger.  How much easier can it get then opening an app, selecting the device you want to display and then starting your lesson without having to think about it again?</p>
        <img class="img-bg" src="https://images.indiegogo.com/file_attachments/674136/files/20140625070048-05-list.png?1403704848">
